etymologies: late 19th century; earliest use found in The Athenaeum. From auto- + either -gravure or French gravure gravure

definitions: A particular form of photoengraving in which a special carbon tissue is used.

notes.text: The process was patented by J. R. Sawyer in 1885, but he does not use the word autogravure in the patent (Brit. Patent 14,855).
